{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Compulsory for an Executor to use a 3rd party bank account for all Estate funds",
        "additional_details": "There is currently very little to no legal protection for the Beneficiaries of a deceased\u2019s Estate. By making this a legal requirement a layer of financial protection is enforced between the 2 parties, Executor and Beneficiary, to ensure the deceased\u2019s final wishes are carried out correctly. The third party account should be in the name of a registered Solicitor/Solicitor Firm who holds a professional position of trust.",
        "background": "Make it a compulsory legal requirement for an Executor of a Will to use a third party bank account for all Estate funds and Assets to provide protection for all Beneficiaries of the Estate.",
